# Privacy Policy for YouTube Live Sub Counter

**Effective date:** [DATE — e.g. 28 April 2026]

This policy describes what information the **YouTube Live Counts** Android
app ("the app") collects, how it is used, and who it is shared with.

## 1. Information the app collects

The app itself does **not** ask you to sign in, create an account, or
provide personal information. It does not request access to your contacts,
photos, files, location, microphone, or camera. The only Android
permission it uses is **Internet access**.

The app does, however, include the **Google AdMob** advertising SDK, which
automatically collects the following data type:

- **Device or other IDs** — specifically your Android Advertising ID (a
  resettable identifier provided by Google Play services).

This identifier is collected and shared with Google so that AdMob can
deliver advertising and detect invalid traffic and fraud. It is not used
to identify you personally and you can reset or delete it at any time
through your device's settings (**Settings → Privacy → Ads**).

All data collected by the app is transmitted over encrypted (HTTPS)
connections.

## 2. How the data is used

The Android Advertising ID collected via AdMob is used for:

- Showing advertisements (including non-personalised ads where required).
- Measuring ad performance.
- Preventing fraud and invalid traffic.
- Complying with applicable laws.

The app itself does not log analytics, crash reports, or any other usage
data on its own servers.

## 3. Third-party services

The app communicates with the following third parties:

- **Google AdMob** — to display ads. Google's handling of this data is
  governed by Google's Privacy Policy:
  https://policies.google.com/privacy and
  https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543.
- **Public YouTube live-count APIs** (mixerno.space, socialcounts.org,
  livecounts.io) — when you look up a channel, the channel handle or ID
  you typed is sent to these services so they can return the channel's
  current subscriber and view counts. These requests include your IP
  address as part of normal HTTPS traffic but no other personal data.
- **Google Play image CDN** (play-lh.googleusercontent.com) — used to
  load the icons and screenshots shown on the "More apps" screen.

The app does not share data with any other third party.

## 4. Children

The app is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly
collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a
child has provided personal information through the app, please contact
us at [YOUR EMAIL] and we will take appropriate action.

## 5. Your choices

- **Reset or delete your advertising ID:** Android Settings → Privacy →
  Ads.
- **Opt out of personalised ads:** same screen ("Opt out of Ads
  Personalisation"), or via the in-app consent dialog if shown.
- **Stop all data sharing:** uninstall the app.

## 6. Data retention and deletion

The app stores no personal data on its own servers. Data handled by
Google AdMob is retained according to Google's policies linked above.
To request deletion of any data associated with your advertising ID,
contact us at [YOUR EMAIL] or use Google's controls at
https://myaccount.google.com.

## 7. Changes to this policy

We may update this policy from time to time. The "Effective date" at the
top of the page will reflect the latest revision. Continued use of the
app after a change constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
